README: Examining Intrahemispheric Parietal-Motor Interconnectivity During Motor Imagery Using Dual-Coil Transcranial Magnetic Stimulation
Project Overview
This project investigates the intrahemispheric connectivity between the posterior parietal cortex (PPC; specifically the supramarginal gyrus) and primary motor cortex (M1) during motor imagery using dual-coil transcranial magnetic stimulation (TMS). A secondary aim was to determine whether a guided motor imagery script (LSRT) produces stronger PPC-M1 interactions than a standard motor imagery script.
