Repository Structure
├── data/
│   ├── data_raw/          # Raw electrophysiological files (.cfs, .sgrx) per participant
│   └── data_processed/
│       ├── MEP_long.csv   # Processed long-format MEP data used in analysis
│       └── DATA_DICTIONARY
├── docs/
│   ├── draft_manuscript.Rmd   # R Markdown manuscript with embedded analysis
│   ├── draft_manuscript.html  # Rendered manuscript
│   ├── references.bib         # Zotero-exported BibTeX references
│   └── apa.csl                # APA citation style file
├── scripts/
│   └── test_script.R      # MEP analysis: paired t-tests, effect sizes, plots
├── Dictionarys/
│   └── DATA_DICTIONARY    # Variable descriptions
├── renv.lock              # Package environment lockfile
└── data_reproducibility.Rproj
Data Description
data/data_processed/MEP_long.csv contains trial-level MEP amplitude data in long format with the following columns:
ColumnDescriptionparticipant_idParticipant identifier (p01, p02, p03, ...)conditionTMS condition: TS (test stimulus / M1-only), 4ms, or 8ms (ISI for dual-coil)mep_amplitudeMEP amplitude (mV) for each individual trialscriptMotor imagery script: standard or LSRT (guided)
Raw data files (.cfs, .sgrx) are named by participant, visit, ISI, and block (e.g., 001_V1_4ms_standard_B1). Raw data are not publicly accessible due to the inclusion of potentially sensitive human participant data.
Reproducing the Analysis
This project uses renv for package management. To restore the environment:
rrenv::restore()
Required packages

dplyr
ggplot2
effsize

Steps

Open data_reproducibility.Rproj in RStudio
Run renv::restore() to install required packages
Open scripts/test_script.R and run to reproduce statistical analyses and figures
Open docs/draft_manuscript.Rmd and knit to reproduce the manuscript

Ethics and Data Availability
Processed data (MEP_long.csv) are not publicly accessible due to the potentially sensitive nature of human participant data. Requests for data access can be directed to [contact info].
